---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { site } from '../lib/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Stroom Performance"
  description="Stroom Performance started on YouTube, wrenching on a real high-altitude drag car. The store exists to sell the parts that actually work where the air runs thin."
>
  <section class="wrap" style="padding-block:3rem 2rem;max-width:48rem;">
    <Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />
    <h1 class="heading-section">Built on the runs, not a catalog.</h1>

    <div class="prose-section" style="margin-top:1.5rem;border-bottom:none;">
      <p>
        Stroom Performance started where a lot of good things do — on the
        internet, wrenching on a race car and posting the results. Cutting a trap
        door with the "Death Wheel" to service a fuel pump. Chasing a converter
        that would actually flash right at altitude. Reading data logs to figure
        out why a run went sideways on an un-prepped surface.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's the whole idea behind the store. Most performance shops assume sea
        level. We don't. Racing at high <span class="hazard">density altitude</span>
        changes everything — the engine fights hypoxia, the converter behaves
        differently, and the fuel math moves. The parts we'll sell are the parts
        that survived those conditions on our own car first.
      </p>
      <h2>Why the niche matters</h2>
      <p>
        Ask most stores for a torque converter and they ask for your car. We ask
        for your car <em>and your altitude</em>. That single question — "will this
        work at my DA?" — is something nobody else answers well. It's the reason
        Stroom exists, and it's the thread that runs through every listing,
        guide, and build on this site.
      </p>
      <h2>What's next</h2>
      <p>
        The storefront is launching in stages as supplier accounts come online.
        In the meantime, the <a href="/guides">guides</a> and
        <a href="/builds">builds</a> carry the expertise, and the
        <a href={site.youtube} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube channel</a>
        keeps documenting the work. Manufacturers and distributors who want in
        can <a href="/wholesale">start a wholesale inquiry</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
